'''Avi Yashchin''' is an American businessman and entrepreneur. He founded CleanEdison, a New York-based green-jobs vocational education company, in 2008. One of the main purposes of the company is the provide clean innovation solutions to underserved areas.<ref>Porter, Jane. [http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/222959 "How to Make the Move From Big-Business Employee to Small-Business Owner"], ''[[Entrepreneur (magazine)]]'', 24 February 2012. Retrieved on 2 March 2015.</ref> Yashchin is currently an Instructor with [[General Assembly (school)|General Assembly]],<ref>generalassemb.ly [https://generalassemb.ly/instructors/avi-yashchin/4110 "GA Instructors"], Retrieved on 16 April 2015.</ref> and has previously worked for [[Barclays Investment Bank|Barclay's Capital]] and [[Lehman Brothers]].<ref>Bindrim, Kira. [http://www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20090902/SMALLBIZ/909029989/ex-lehman-execs-set-up-their-own-shops "Ex-Lehman execs set up their own shops"], Crain’s New York Business, 2 September 2009. Retrieved on 5 March 2015.</ref> He received his MBA from the Stern School of Business at New York University.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=117969449&privcapId=117969424&previousCapId=117969424&previousTitle=CleanEdison,%2520Inc "Avi Yashchin Executive Profile"], Bloomberg Business, Retrieved on 11 March 2015.</ref>
