{{short description|Tool for assessing opacity and contrast ratio of coatings}}
{{unreferenced|date=January 2011}}
'''Drawdown cards''' are used for testing [[paint]]s and [[coating]]s through [[wet film]] preparation.

Black and white cards are used to measure both [[Opacity (optics)|opacity]] and [[contrast ratio]]. By measuring reflectance values of both parts of the card one can gain a quantitative opacity value of a paint sample.

